  Historically, the profession of geriatric nurse has arisen from the care of the sick and has developed very differently from region to region. A question as to the status of development of the profession of geriatric nurse cannot be answered by reference to the current status of legislation on professional law matters. If experts in that field focus too long on such matters, there is a danger that decisive developments in the profession of geriatric nurse take place outside their field of vision.  
